HEADWORD: Chute
<hw>Chute</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>chute</ets>,
prop. a fall.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A framework, trough, or tube, upon
or through which objects are made to slide from a higher to a lower
level, or through which water passes to a wheel.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>See <er>Shoot</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

